# Architecture (do not break)

Production uses **PostgreSQL** when `DATABASE_URL` is set (Docker Compose default).

- **Portfolio data**: `holdings`, `purchase_journal`, `monthly_deposits`, `net_dividends`, `dividend_receipts` ‚Äî per `user_id`.
- **Market library**: `stock_documents` ‚Äî shared JSONB; access via `services.shared_market_db`.
- **Legacy** `/data/users/`, `/data/vectordb/`: import-only (`scripts/migrate_to_cloud_sql.py`), never runtime writes.

## Forbidden without explicit user request

- Re-introducing Chroma or per-user SQLite as production storage
- Direct `VectorStore(persist_directory=...)` in services/UI (use `shared_market_db`)
- `date.fromisoformat(row[...])` on Postgres query results
- Separate `PortfolioStore()` + `PurchaseJournalStore()` without shared `db_path`
- Skipping migration SQL when adding tables/columns
- Setting global `DATABASE_URL` in unit tests (use `PYTEST_USE_SQLITE` in `tests/conftest.py`)

